history.content:
Well, I'm not going to take time to go confirm whether the information you read on calcentral is the same information I could read on calcentral but I will try to explain what I think happened with your waitlist position:

When students currently enrolled in the class decide to switch discussion sections if there is any waitlist on their desired new section and/or if it is full, they are kicked out of the class and moved to position #1 on the waitlist.  Everyone currently on the waitlist is moved one spot back.  Unless the previously enrolled person chose the discussion section you are currently waitlisted for, it doesn't change your chances of eventually being enrolled.

Can anyone explain why this happened? Also I checked the class on calcentral recently, and there seems to be 26 spots left with 72 people on the waitlist.Is this an accurate assessment so far? I really need to take this class and am worried about moving further up on the waitlist. Can someone help with how to take care of this issue? Thanks!
